label: Measurements
comment: Measurements associated with this terminal defining  where the measurement is placed in the network topology.  It may be used, for instance, to capture the sensor position, such as a voltage transformer (PT) at a busbar or a current transformer (CT) at the bar between a breaker and an isolator.

label: AccumulatorValues
comment: The values connected to this measurement.

label: LimitSets
comment: A measurement may have zero or more limit ranges defined for it.

label: LimitSet
comment: The set of limits.

label: value
comment: The value to supervise against. The value is positive.

label: Limits
comment: The limit values used for supervision of Measurements.

label: Measurements
comment: The Measurements using the LimitSet.

label: AccumulatorValue
comment: The accumulator value that is reset by the command.

label: Accumulator
comment: Measurement to which this value is connected.

label: AccumulatorReset
comment: The command that resets the accumulator value.

label: AnalogValues
comment: The values connected to this measurement.

label: LimitSets
comment: A measurement may have zero or more limit ranges defined for it.

label: positiveFlowIn
comment: If true then this measurement is an active power, reactive power or current with the convention that a positive value measured at the Terminal means power is flowing into the related PowerSystemResource.

label: AnalogValue
comment: The MeasurementValue that is controlled.

label: maxValue
comment: Normal value range maximum for any of the Control.value. Used for scaling, e.g. in bar graphs.

label: minValue
comment: Normal value range minimum for any of the Control.value. Used for scaling, e.g. in bar graphs.

label: LimitSet
comment: The set of limits.

label: value
comment: The value to supervise against.

label: Limits
comment: The limit values used for supervision of Measurements.

label: Measurements
comment: The Measurements using the LimitSet.

label: Analog
comment: Measurement to which this value is connected.

label: AnalogControl
comment: The Control variable associated with the MeasurementValue.

label: DiscreteValue
comment: The MeasurementValue that is controlled.

label: ValueAliasSet
comment: The ValueAliasSet used for translation of a Control value to a name.

label: normalValue
comment: Normal value for Control.value e.g. used for percentage scaling.

label: value
comment: The value representing the actuator output.

label: PowerSystemResource
comment: Regulating device governed by this control output.

label: controlType
comment: Specifies the type of Control. For example, this specifies if the Control represents BreakerOpen, BreakerClose, GeneratorVoltageSetPoint, GeneratorRaise, GeneratorLower, etc.

label: operationInProgress
comment: Indicates that a client is currently sending control commands that has not completed.

label: timeStamp
comment: The last time a control output was sent.

label: unitMultiplier
comment: The unit multiplier of the controlled quantity.

label: unitSymbol
comment: The unit of measure of the controlled quantity.

label: DiscreteValues
comment: The values connected to this measurement.

label: ValueAliasSet
comment: The ValueAliasSet used for translation of a MeasurementValue.value to a name.

label: Command
comment: The Control variable associated with the MeasurementValue.

label: Discrete
comment: Measurement to which this value is connected.

label: description
comment: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: isPercentageLimits
comment: Tells if the limit values are in percentage of normalValue or the specified Unit for Measurements and Controls.

label: PowerSystemResource
comment: The power system resource that contains the measurement.

label: Terminal
comment: One or more measurements may be associated with a terminal in the network.

label: measurementType
comment:
Specifies the type of measurement.  For example, this specifies if the measurement represents an indoor temperature, outdoor temperature, bus voltage, line flow, etc.
When the measurementType is set to "Specialization", the type of Measurement is defined in more detail by the specialized class which inherits from Measurement.

label: phases
comment:
Indicates to which phases the measurement applies and avoids the need to use 'measurementType' to also encode phase information (which would explode the types). The phase information in Measurement, along with 'measurementType' and 'phases' uniquely defines a Measurement for a device, based on normal network phase. Their meaning will not change when the computed energizing phasing is changed due to jumpers or other reasons.
If the attribute is missing three phases (ABC) shall be assumed.

label: unitMultiplier
comment: The unit multiplier of the measured quantity.

label: unitSymbol
comment: The unit of measure of the measured quantity.

label: MeasurementValueQuality
comment: A MeasurementValue has a MeasurementValueQuality associated with it.

label: MeasurementValueSource
comment: A reference to the type of source that updates the MeasurementValue, e.g. SCADA, CCLink, manual, etc. User conventions for the names of sources are contained in the introduction to IEC 61970-301.

label: sensorAccuracy
comment: The limit, expressed as a percentage of the sensor maximum, that errors will not exceed when the sensor is used under  reference conditions.

label: timeStamp
comment: The time when the value was last updated.

label: MeasurementValue
comment: A MeasurementValue has a MeasurementValueQuality associated with it.

label: MeasurementValues
comment: The MeasurementValues updated by the source.

label: Controls
comment: The controller outputs used to actually govern a regulating device, e.g. the magnetization of a synchronous machine or capacitor bank breaker actuator.

label: Measurements
comment: The measurements associated with this power system resource.

label: badReference
comment: Measurement value may be incorrect due to a reference being out of calibration.

label: estimatorReplaced
comment: Value has been replaced by State Estimator. estimatorReplaced is not an IEC61850 quality bit but has been put in this class for convenience.

label: failure
comment: This identifier indicates that a supervision function has detected an internal or external failure, e.g. communication failure.

label: oldData
comment: Measurement value is old and possibly invalid, as it has not been successfully updated during a specified time interval.

label: operatorBlocked
comment: Measurement value is blocked and hence unavailable for transmission.

label: oscillatory
comment: To prevent some overload of the communication it is sensible to detect and suppress oscillating (fast changing) binary inputs. If a signal changes in a defined time twice in the same direction (from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0) then oscillation is detected and the detail quality identifier "oscillatory" is set. If it is detected a configured numbers of transient changes could be passed by. In this time the validity status "questionable" is set. If after this defined numbers of changes the signal is still in the oscillating state the value shall be set either to the opposite state of the previous stable value or to a defined default value. In this case the validity status "questionable" is reset and "invalid" is set as long as the signal is oscillating. If it is configured such that no transient changes should be passed by then the validity status "invalid" is set immediately in addition to the detail quality identifier "oscillatory" (used for status information only).

label: outOfRange
comment: Measurement value is beyond a predefined range of value.

label: overFlow
comment: Measurement value is beyond the capability of being  represented properly. For example, a counter value overflows from maximum count back to a value of zero.

label: source
comment: Source gives information related to the origin of a value. The value may be acquired from the process, defaulted or substituted.

label: suspect
comment: A correlation function has detected that the value is not consistent with other values. Typically set by a network State Estimator.

label: test
comment: Measurement value is transmitted for test purposes.

label: validity
comment: Validity of the measurement value.

label: ValueAliasSet
comment: The ValueAliasSet used for translation of a Control value to a name.

label: normalValue
comment: Normal value for Control.value e.g. used for percentage scaling.

label: value
comment: The value representing the actuator output.

label: StringMeasurementValues
comment: The values connected to this measurement.

label: StringMeasurement
comment: Measurement to which this value is connected.

label: Commands
comment: The Commands using the set for translation.

label: Discretes
comment: The Measurements using the set for translation.

label: RaiseLowerCommands
comment: The Commands using the set for translation.

label: Values
comment: The ValueToAlias mappings included in the set.

label: ValueAliasSet
comment: The ValueAliasSet having the ValueToAlias mappings.

label: value
comment: The value that is mapped.
